Section 14: Spring Application Events
    Lecture 76: Publish and Consume Spring Custom Events: Login Failure event

1. Create New LoginFailureEvent.java file
  - ej.springframework.services.security.LoginFailureEvent.java
  - This class extends Application Event

2. Create New LoginFailureEventPublisher.java
  - ej.springframework.services.security.LoginFailureEventPublisher.java
  - This class implements ApplicationEventPublisherAware class
  - Add @Component annotation above the LoginFailureEventPublisher class

3. Create New LoginFailureEventHandler.java
  - ej.springframework.services.security.LoginFailureEventHandler.java
  - This class implements ApplicationListener<LoginFailureEvent> class
  - Add @Component annotation above the LoginFailureEventHandler class
  - Override method onApplicationEvent(..)

4. Autowiring in the LoginAspect.java
  4.1 Declare LoginFailureEventPublisher constructor ?
  4.2 Implements setter method
  4.3 Add @Autowired annotation above the setter method
  4.4 Implements throw Call LoginFailureEvent Exception

5. Test
 5.1 Start SpringmvcApplication Server
 5.2 Open the Browser
 5.3 Try Login with wrong id and password
 5.4 Check the SpringmvcApplication Server console
    - Result:
      This is before the Authenticate Method: authentication: false
      Login failed for user: test
      LoginEvent Failure for: test


